paragraphs.text:
%sh

# steps to download the dataset
# create the local download directory if does not exist
mkdir -p ~/data-downloads
rm ~/data-downloads/*.csv

# create the required HDFS directory
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p /user/cloudera/data/raw/crime/chicago

# download the data from Chicago city data website
wget -O ~/data-downloads/crime_chicago.csv https://data.cityofchicago.org/api/views/ijzp-q8t2/rows.csv?accessType=DOWNLOAD 

# copy the file to HDFS
hdfs dfs -put -f ~/data-downloads/crime_chicago.csv /user/cloudera/data/raw/crime/chicago/

# delete local data files
rm ~/data-downloads/*.csv

paragraphs.title: Creating the database and Hive external table
paragraphs.text:
%hive

CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS crime_db;

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS crime_db.chicago_crime_raw;
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crime_db.chicago_crime_raw (
    ID int,
    CaseNumber string,
    Date string,
    Block string,
    IUCR string,
    PrimaryType string,
    Description string,
    LocationDescription string,
    Arrest string,
    Domestic string,
    Beat string,
    District string,
    Ward string,
    CommunityArea string,
    FBICode string,
    XCoordinate int,
    YCoordinate int,
    Year int,
    UpdatedOn string,
    Latitude float,
    Longitude float,
    Location string
)
ROW FORMAT SERDE 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.OpenCSVSerde'
WITH SERDEPROPERTIES (
   "separatorChar" = ",",
   "quoteChar"     = "\"",
   "escapeChar"    = "\\"
)  
STORED AS TEXTFILE
LOCATION '/user/cloudera/data/raw/crime/chicago'
TBLPROPERTIES ("skip.header.line.count"="1")

paragraphs.title: Creating the partitioned table
paragraphs.text:
%hive

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned (
    ID int,
    CaseNumber string,
    Date string,
    Block string,
    IUCR string,
    PrimaryType string,
    Description string,
    LocationDescription string,
    Arrest string,
    Domestic string,
    Beat string,
    District string,
    Ward string,
    CommunityArea string,
    FBICode string,
    XCoordinate int,
    YCoordinate int,
    UpdatedOn string,
    Latitude float,
    Longitude float,
    Location string
)
PARTITIONED BY (year int)
STORED AS PARQUET;

paragraphs.title: Loading the partitioned table
paragraphs.text:
%hive

SET hive.exec.dynamic.partition=true; 
SET hive.exec.dynamic.partition.mode=nonstrict;

INSERT OVERWRITE TABLE  crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned PARTITION(Year)
    SELECT 
        ID,
        CaseNumber,
        from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(Date , 'MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss a')), 
        Block,
        IUCR,
        PrimaryType,
        Description,
        LocationDescription,
        Arrest,
        Domestic,
        Beat,
        District,
        Ward,
        CommunityArea,
        FBICode,
        XCoordinate,
        YCoordinate,
        from_unixtime(unix_timestamp(UpdatedOn , 'MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss a')),
        Latitude,
        Longitude,
        Location,
        Year
    FROM
        crime_db.chicago_crime_raw;

SET hive.exec.dynamic.partition.mode=strict;

paragraphs.title: Comparing Current YTD to Previous YTD incidents by Primary Type
paragraphs.text:
%hive

select 
    coalesce(prev_year.primarytype, curr_year.primarytype) primarytype,
    coalesce(prev_year.total_incidents_prev_ytd, 0) prev_ytd_incidents,
    coalesce(curr_year.total_incidents_curr_ytd,0) curr_ytd_incidents,
    round(((coalesce(curr_year.total_incidents_curr_ytd,0) - coalesce(prev_year.total_incidents_prev_ytd, 0))/coalesce(prev_year.total_incidents_prev_ytd, 0))*100,2) percent_increase
from 
    (select primarytype, count(*) total_incidents_prev_ytd 
     from crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned 
     where year = year(current_date)-1 and date_format(date, 'MM-dd') <= date_format(current_date, 'MM-dd')
     group by primarytype
    ) prev_year 
full outer join
    (select primarytype, count(*) total_incidents_curr_ytd 
     from crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned 
     where year = year(current_date) and date_format(date, 'MM-dd') <= date_format(current_date, 'MM-dd')
     group by primarytype
    ) curr_year on prev_year.primarytype = curr_year.primarytype
order by percent_increase desc
limit ${TopN=5,5|10|15|20|25};

paragraphs.title: Comparing Current MTD to Previous MTD incidents by Primary Type
paragraphs.text:
%hive

select
    coalesce(prev_mtd.primarytype, curr_mtd.primarytype) primarytype,
    coalesce(prev_mtd.total_incidents_prev_mtd, 0) prev_mtd_incidents,
    coalesce(curr_mtd.total_incidents_curr_mtd,0) curr_mtd_incidents,
    round(((coalesce(curr_mtd.total_incidents_curr_mtd,0) - coalesce(prev_mtd.total_incidents_prev_mtd, 0))/coalesce(prev_mtd.total_incidents_prev_mtd, 0))*100,2) percent_increase
from 
    (select primarytype, count(*) total_incidents_prev_mtd 
     from crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned 
     where year = year(add_months(current_date(), -1))
        and date >= date_add(add_months(current_date(),-1),1-day(add_months(current_date(),-1)))
        and date <= date_add(add_months(current_date(), -1) ,1)
     group by primarytype
    ) prev_mtd
full outer join
    (select primarytype, count(*) total_incidents_curr_mtd 
     from crime_db.chicago_crime_partitioned 
     where year = year(current_date()) 
        and date >= date_add(current_date(),1-day(current_date()))
        and date <= date_add(current_date(),1)
     group by primarytype
    ) curr_mtd on prev_mtd.primarytype = curr_mtd.primarytype
order by curr_mtd_incidents desc;
